Qualifications:
1. A bachelor's degree in Human Resource Management, Organizational Behavior or Development, Business or Public Administration, the Applied Behavioral Sciences, Industrial Relations or a job-related course of study determined by the appointing authority;
2. Valid Certification as a Professional in Human Resource awarded by the Human Resource Certification Institute, and one-year Human Resource experience;
3. Three years Human Resource paraprofessional or technical-level experience.
4. The State Certified Human Resources Professional (SCHRP) certification, awarded by the Oregon Chief Human Resources Office, substitutes for six months of human resource professional-level experience.
5. Valid certification as a SHRM Certified Professional awarded by a nationally recognized organization, or valid certification as a PSHRA-CP from the Public Sector HR Association substitutes for one year of human resource professional-level experience.
